@sijie with pulsar-client-original it complains about

org.apache.pulsar.client.api.PulsarClientException$BrokerPersistenceException: org.apache.bookkeeper.mledger.ManagedLedgerException: Not enough non-faulty bookies available
at org.apache.pulsar.client.api.PulsarClientException.unwrap(PulsarClientException.java:845)

@pg2404 I understand the motivation. However, I am not sure we are implementing this in the right way. 

In your use case, can't you use batchReceive to receive a batch of messages and ack the whole batch?

If we want to enhance the API to support batch acknowledgment, doesn't it make more sense to support

```
ack(List<Message> msgs);
ack(List<Messages> msgBatches);
```

@xiaomin0322 If bc is already included in other module, you could exclude `bouncy-castle-bc-shaded`.

http://pulsar.apache.org/docs/en/security-bouncy-castle/#exclude-bc-non-fips-and-include-bc-fips
https://github.com/apache/pulsar/blob/master/bouncy-castle/bcfips-include-test/pom.xml#L47

